      • getTypeArgument

        public static <T> java.lang.reflect.Type getTypeArgument(java.lang.reflect.Type type,
                                                         java.lang.Class<T> toClass,
                                                         java.lang.reflect.TypeVariable<java.lang.Class<T>> typeVariable)
        Gets a single type argument, resolved to a class, from the set of type arguments of a class/interface based on a the toClass subtype. For instance, given the parameterised type representing Map&lt;String,Integer&gt; , the toClass value of Map.class, and the typeVariable of Map.class.getTypeParameters()[0], then this method will return String.class. This method will work even if the type represented by type is a subtype of the required type and does not itself have any template arguments. For example, this method will determine that both of the parameters for the interface Map are Object for the subtype Properties even though the subtype does not directly implement the Map interface. If the type is not a parameterised type, but a raw Class then the method will return Object.class

        This method throws IllegalArgumentException if type is not assignable to toClass. It returns an Object.class if the actual type parameter can not be determined.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of toClass
        Parameters:
        type - the type from which to determine the type parameters of toClass
        toClass - the class whose type parameter is to be determined based on the subtype type
        typeVariable - the specific typeVariable of toClass to retrieve.
        Returns:
        the Class of the type argument, or null if type is not assignable to toClass
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if type is not assignable to toClass.
